---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import TextBlock from "../components/TextBlock.astro";
---

<Layout title="Teaching — Gabriel Forn-Cuní">

  <PageHeader
    title="Teaching"
    gradient="bg-gradient-amber-teal"
    description="My academic positions have always been research-only, but I have actively engaged in teaching, and mentoring."
  />

  <Section class="py-12">
    <TextBlock>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-4">Teaching</h2>
      <p class="mt-6">
        I coordinated and lectured courses as part of the MSc in Biology at Leiden University, and
        participated as a teacher in other BSc and MSc level courses both at Leiden University and
        Universitat de Barcelona:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-4 list-disc list-outside ml-5">
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">Mechanisms of Disease</span>,
          MSc in Biology, Leiden University (2024–2025). Course coordinator; conventional lectures and
          invited-speaker seminars. 85 students, 6 ECTS. Course rating 8.4; teacher evaluation 9.3.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">Mechanisms of Disease</span>,
          MSc in Biology, Leiden University (2023–2024). Participant teacher throughout the course.
          90 students, 6 ECTS. Course rating 7.5; teacher evaluation 8.1.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">Model organisms in cancer drug discovery and development</span>,
          MSc in Bio-Pharmaceutical Sciences, Leiden University (2025–2026, 2024–2025 and 2023–2024).
          Participant teacher, one specialist lecture. 40 students, 4 ECTS. Teacher evaluation 8.3
          (2024–2025).
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">Cell Biology and Cancer</span>,
          BSc in Biology, Leiden University (2022–2023). Practical laboratory supervisor; lectures and
          practicals. 100 students, 3 ECTS.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">Mecanismos de Patogenicidad Microbiana</span>,
          MSc in Microbiología Avanzada, Universitat de Barcelona (2016–2017). Participant teacher,
          one specialist lecture.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </TextBlock>
  </Section>

  <Section class="py-12">
    <TextBlock>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-4">Mentoring</h2>
      <p class="mt-6">
        I regularly supervise visiting scientists, bachelor, master, and PhD students:
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6">
        At the doctoral level, I am the co-promotor of
        <a href="https://www.universiteitleiden.nl/en/staffmembers/yun-zhang#tab-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="transition-colors hover:text-accent-cyan">Yun Zhang</a>'s
        PhD thesis, together with Prof.
        <a href="https://www.universiteitleiden.nl/en/staffmembers/alexander-kros#tab-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="transition-colors hover:text-accent-magenta">Alexander Kros</a>
        (Leiden Institute of Chemistry, Leiden University). Yun is developing liposomal formulations
        for the targeted delivery of drugs across the blood-brain barrier and to specific macrophage
        populations, which we test in the zebrafish model system that I developed within the
        collaborative NWO-XL project; she is expected to defend her thesis in 2026.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6">
        I have also mentored more than 14 MSc and BSc students, all with outstanding evaluations which allowed
        them to take on PhD positions at prestigious institutions, including several cum laude, and
        national research prizes for the internship carried out under my supervision.
      </p>
    </TextBlock>
  </Section>

</Layout>
